[{"body": "@jbornschein @nouiz Here's my proposal for dealing with unknown configurations. It gives a warning, but only if the unknown configuration is a likely typo. Otherwise it just silently ignores it. I prefer this over giving warnings each time a user doesn't import `blocks.extras` (regardless of whether this warning is given at import or at exit), but it's slightly more user-friendly than being entirely silent.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/111210820", "created_at": "2015-06-11T17:14:14Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/712#issuecomment-111210820", "updated_at": "2015-06-11T17:14:29Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/bartvm", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2299595?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "bartvm", "type": "User", "id": 2299595, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/followers"}, "id": 111210820, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/712"}, {"body": "Good direction, but how do you define typo?\n\nOn Thu, Jun 11, 2015 at 1:14 PM, Bart van Merri\u00ebnboer <\nnotifications@github.com> wrote:\n\n> @jbornschein <https://github.com/jbornschein> @nouiz\n> <https://github.com/nouiz> Here's my proposal for dealing with unknown\n> configurations. It gives a warning, but only if the unknown configuration\n> is a likely typo. Otherwise it just silently ignores it. I prefer this over\n> giving warnings each time a user doesn't import blocks.extras (regardless\n> of whether this warning is given at imports or at exit), but it's slightly\n> more user-friendly than being entirely silent.\n>\n> \u2014\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> <https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/712#issuecomment-111210820>.\n>\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/111218342", "created_at": "2015-06-11T17:40:50Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/712#issuecomment-111218342", "updated_at": "2015-06-11T17:40:50Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/nouiz", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/180987?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "nouiz", "type": "User", "id": 180987, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/followers"}, "id": 111218342, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/712"}, {"body": "I use [`difflib.get_close_matches`](https://docs.python.org/2/library/difflib.html#difflib.get_close_matches) with the default threshold of 0.6, which is quite sensitive (for example, `some_other_backend` is a match to `log_backend`). (Matching with edit-distance might be better, but that's not in the standard library.) For now, that seems to work well, because the few configurations we have are all quite different.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/111222378", "created_at": "2015-06-11T17:53:20Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/712#issuecomment-111222378", "updated_at": "2015-06-11T17:53:20Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/bartvm", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2299595?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "bartvm", "type": "User", "id": 2299595, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bartvm/followers"}, "id": 111222378, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/712"}, {"body": "This seem good. I didn't know about that lib. I made a ticket in Theano about this: https://github.com/Theano/Theano/issues/3021", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/111232562", "created_at": "2015-06-11T18:28:15Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/712#issuecomment-111232562", "updated_at": "2015-06-11T18:28:15Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/nouiz", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/180987?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "nouiz", "type": "User", "id": 180987, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nouiz/followers"}, "id": 111232562, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/712"}, {"body": "I guess that works -- it solves the problem. And it uses a stdlib that I didn't know about.\r\n\r\nBut in general I feel a bit uncanny when it comes to \"software wants to be clever about variable or configuration-option names\". I think of configuration parsers as simple pieces of software that do something very deterministic and that should not surprise me. And when I ever see a message like \"unknown configuration option\" I would expect that I will always get such a warning. Not only when the given option is sufficiently similar to an actual option.\r\n\r\nAccording to my judgement I would prefer to simply try to import `blocks.extra`. And rather deal with the surprises that might pop up as a result of that.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/comments/111260313", "created_at": "2015-06-11T20:03:27Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/mila-udem/blocks/pull/712#issuecomment-111260313", "updated_at": "2015-06-12T12:45:40Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jbornschein", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/241247?v=3", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "jbornschein", "type": "User", "id": 241247, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jbornschein/followers"}, "id": 111260313, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mila-udem/blocks/issues/712"}]